Rooted in responsibility, driven by purpose

WHO WE ARE

We are the world’s leading standard-setting organisation for the jewellery and watch industry

Founded in 2005, by 14 organisations including De Beers, Tiffany & Co., and Cartier, we unite over 2,000 companies across the entire global watch and jewellery supply chain, to promote responsible practices and ethical standards. We advance trust, transparency, and sustainability, benefiting consumers, communities, and the environment.

OUR STORY
WHAT WE DO

The jewellery and watch industry has a larger ambition to contribute to a better, fairer world

We drive change by helping companies embed responsible practices into daily operations. Members follow one or more of three standards: the Code of Practices (COP), Chain of Custody (COC), and Laboratory Grown Material Standard (LGMS). By implementing our standards, members support the UN 2030 Agenda and the 17 Sustainable Development Goals.

OUR STANDARDS
BECOME A MEMBER

Membership is your pathway to sustainable growth​

Sustainability is a journey of continuous improvement. RJC membership gives you the opportunity to accelerate yours. What differentiates us is that we have one solution for businesses, big or small, to integrate sustainability in its operations. Our standards cover human rights, labour rights, health and safety, product integrity and many other key topics.

RJC AT 20

Celebrating 20 years of Responsible Jewellery

In 2025, we’re celebrating our 20th anniversary. A huge shoutout to our incredible members who are committed to transforming our industry. We’ve officially reached 2,000 members and couldn’t be more excited to welcome even more of you in the next 20 years.
